\chapter{Introduction}


Postal History and stamps of Kosovo is divided into periods corresponding to the postal system of Serbia (Yugoslavia), within which was an autonomous province of Kosovo and Metohija, under the Transitional Kosovo mission of the United Nations (1999 - 2007) and partially recognized Republic of Kosovo (since 2008).

## The Republic of Kosovo

The first stamps of the partially recognized Republic of Kosovo came shortly after independence on 7 March 2008. A series of two stamps dedicated to Teacher's Day. They were given an inscription in three languages, Albanian, English and Serbian : "Republic of Kosovo", the nominal value specified in the euro. 

