Post and telephone - Telegraph Service (PTT) in Kosovo was established 21 December 1959 goda decision of the Governing Council of the Yugoslav PTT and with the approval of the Executive Council of the People's Republic of Serbia on 18 December 1959 year. For the first time PTT "Kosovo" was registered as a company 25 on March 1960 goda. [1]

Before 1960, the post of Kosovo has provided postal services in all cities the region, the countryside is not serviced. After creating the solid surface "Kosovo", the postal service is initially not changed significantly. Extensive development of postal, telephone and telegraph communications Kosovo began only after 1974. At the end of 1980 for the needs of PTT "Kosovo" were built 75 modern buildings with a total area of over 60,000 mÂ², as well as head office building in Pristina area of over 11,500 square meters. [1]

Of September 13 1990 goda PTT "Kosovo" was included into the structure of PTT "Serbia" as a unit of PTT "Pristina" and was so until 1998. According to today's Kosovo authorities, the integration was accompanied by the dismissal of postal employees Albanian and other non-Serbs.

